name: Polyol ether, for flexible foam polyurethane production, at plant, CTR
description: Heat is a coproduct for the production of polyether polyol for use in flexible foam polyurethane. The energy for exported heat was reported separately as recovered energy.  Complete inventory data and metadata are available in full in the final report and appendices, Cradle-to-Gate Life Cycle Inventory of Nine Plastic Resins and Four Polyurethane Precursors. This report has been extensively reviewed within Franklin Associates and has undergone partial critical review by ACC Plastics Division members and is available at: www.americanchemistry.com. Quantities may vary slightly between the reference to main source and and this module due to rounding. Important note: although most of the data in the US LCI database has undergone some sort of review, the database as a whole has not yet undergone a formal validation process.  Please email comments to lci@nrel.gov.

category.name: All Other Basic Organic Chemical Manufacturing

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Reaction of polyol initiator with hydroxide catalyst and propylene oxide and ethylene oxide, followed by separation and purification by distillation
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data are from both primary and secondary sources.  Data for the production of polyether polyol were provided by five leading producers (5 plants) in North America.  The polyether polyol producers who provided data for this module verified that the characteristics of their plants are representative of a majority of the North American production.
